parameters: Banka: "Miss Umi? Could it be that you're feeling unwell?"
Umi: "Uh... yeah... haa haa... ngh... I just want to... rest a bit."
Kru: "This is serious! You're sweating profusely! Let's take a break!"

Umi: "Ah... I'm okay... Kru... ugh... you might... smell the sweat... don't
come... too close..."
Kru: "I don't mind that at all."
Umi: "Ah... haa... it's Umi who... cares..."
Banka: "Then I'll go prepare some medicine and food right away!"
Kru: "Banka! I'm going to fetch some water! Take care of Umi!"
Kru "Where did both of you go?"

Kru "Hmm, they're late... I don't want to miss them, but... should I go
look for them...?"
Kru "Banka! Where have you been! And Umi⁉"

Banka "Ah, Umi-san said she was going to relieve herself. I thought I'd
take the chance to go pick some fruit. Hasn't she come back yet?"
Kru "Ah... I'm worried... I'm going to look for her!"

Banka "Ah! Wait a second! Umi-san said if anyone followed her when she
went, she'd kill them with a fierce glare, so if you bump into her, I'll
get scolded."

Banka "Besides, she looked better when she left, and her voice was strong,
so I don't think there's anything to worry about. Let's wait a little
longer."

Kru "Is that so... Yeah, you're right. Just imagining running into Umi
while she's..."

Kru "What do you mean 'what'? Where have you been when you're not feeling
well?"
Umi "Ah... I went to relieve myself."
Kru "Even so, you took too long. I was worried."

Umi "Sorry. I was embarrassed so I went quite far away, and then I got
lost."
Kru "I see. Well, as long as you're safe, that's what matters."

Banka "Well, it's a relief you're safe! Hahaha! Oh? Umi-san, you look much
more refreshed than before."

Banka "And your cheeks are a faint pink color, you must have been holding
it in quite a bit."
Kru "Hey Banka, don't say things like that."
Banka "No, no, my apologies. Come on! You must be hungry. Let's eat."
